race.comment: LADY BLAZINGTON (8) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (17.03) at this track behind Brick And Stick in a Grade 4/5. Has the pace to be prominent. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. One of the contenders. LUCKY BOY BLUE (1) was in the minors two back (20.55) at Grafton but ran below best last time there, finishing 6th. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from four starts. Bold showing expected. CHEEKY TONI (7) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing second behind Misty Bonus (17.10) in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from four attempts. Must be included in calculations. RAMPANI (2) generally performs well from this box.
